<h3 id="goal">Goal</h3>
<p>The goal of this post is to make the <strong>launcher</strong> and the <strong>taskbar</strong> of Ubuntu 16.04 to be transparent</p>

<h3 id="steps">Steps</h3>
<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step1.png" alt="Step" />
First, youâ€™ll start with everything being opaque.</p>
<ol>
  <li>Install Unity Tweak Tool with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo apt-get install unity-tweak-tool</code></li>
  <li>Open Unity Tweak Tool
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step2.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>Click on the â€œLauncherâ€ category
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step3.png" alt="Step" />
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step4.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>Under the â€œAppearanceâ€ section, bring the <em>Transparency Level</em> to 100%
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step5.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>This will make the Launcher to be transparent
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step6.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>Install CompizConfig Settings Manager with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo apt-get install compizconfig-settings-manager</code>
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step7.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>Under the â€œDesktopâ€ section, click on <em>Ubuntu Unity Plugin</em>
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step8.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>At this point, the â€œBackground Colorâ€ should be <strong>black</strong>. Click on the color to change its settings
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step10.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>Bring the â€œOpacityâ€ level down to <strong>1</strong> (If you set it to zero, it will reset the colors in the Launcher)
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step11.png" alt="Step" />
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step12.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>Now the Taskbar should also be transparent. Exit by clicking â€œBackâ€ &gt; â€œCloseâ€
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step13.png" alt="Step" /></li>
  <li>Yay! Done!
<img src="http://localhost:4000/assets/images/transparency/step14.png" alt="Step" /></li>
</ol>
